quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  58,14,Have you not seen those ňĻhypocritesňļ who ally themselves with a people with whom Allah is displeased? They are neither with you nor with them. And they swear to lies knowingly
  58,15,Allah has prepared for them a severe punishment. Evil indeed is what they do
  58,16,"They have made their ňĻfalseňļ oaths as a shield, hindering ňĻothersňļ from the cause of Allah. So they will suffer a humiliating punishment"
  58,17,Neither their wealth nor children will be of any help to them against Allah whatsoever. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  58,18,"On the Day Allah resurrects them all, they will ňĻfalselyňļ swear to Him as they swear to you, thinking they have something to stand on. Indeed, it is they who are the ňĻtotalňļ liars"
  58,19,"Satan has taken hold of them, causing them to forget the remembrance of Allah. They are the party of Satan. Surely Satan‚Äôs party is bound to lose"
  58,20,"ňĻAs forňļ those who defy Allah and His Messenger, they will definitely be among the most debased"
  58,21,"Allah has decreed, ‚ÄúI and My messengers will certainly prevail.‚ÄĚ Surely Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  58,22,"You will never find a people who ňĻtrulyňļ believe in Allah and the Last Day loyal to those who defy Allah and His Messenger, even if they were their parents, children, siblings, or extended family. For those ňĻbelieversňļ, Allah has instilled faith in their hearts and strengthened them with a spirit from Him.¬†He will admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. They are the party of Allah. Indeed, Allah‚Äôs party is bound to succeed"
  59,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth glorifies Allah. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  59,2,"He is the One Who expelled the disbelievers of the People of the Book from their homes for ňĻtheirňļ first banishment ňĻeverňļ. You never thought they would go. And they thought their strongholds would put them out of Allah‚Äôs reach. But ňĻthe decree ofňļ Allah came upon them from where they never expected. And He cast horror into their hearts so they destroyed their houses with their own hands and the hands of the believers.¬†So take a lesson ňĻfrom thisňļ, O people of insight"
  59,3,"Had Allah not decreed exile for them, He would have certainly punished them in this world. And in the Hereafter they will suffer the punishment of the Fire"
  59,4,"This is because they defied Allah and His Messenger. And whoever defies Allah, then Allah is truly severe in punishment"
  59,5,"Whatever palm trees you ňĻbelieversňļ cut down or left standing intact, it was ňĻallňļ by Allah‚Äôs Will, so that He might disgrace the rebellious"
  59,6,As for the gains Allah has turned over to His Messenger from them‚ÄĒyou did not ňĻevenňļ spur on any horse or camel for such gains. But Allah gives authority to His messengers over whoever He wills. For Allah is Most Capable of everything
  59,7,"As for gains granted by Allah to His Messenger from the people of ňĻotherňļ lands, they are for Allah and the Messenger, his close relatives, orphans, the poor, and ňĻneedyňļ travellers so that wealth may not merely circulate among your rich. Whatever the Messenger gives you, take it. And whatever he forbids you from, leave it. And fear Allah. Surely Allah is severe in punishment"
  59,8,"ňĻSome of the gains will beňļ for poor emigrants who were driven out of their homes and wealth, seeking Allah‚Äôs bounty and pleasure, and standing up for Allah and His Messenger. They are the ones true in faith"
  59,9,"As for those who had settled in the city and ňĻembracedňļ the faith before ňĻthe arrival ofňļ the emigrants, they love whoever immigrates to them, never having a desire in their hearts for whatever ňĻof the gainsňļ is given to the emigrants. They give ňĻthe emigrantsňļ preference over themselves even though they may be in need. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ successful"
  59,10,"And those who come after them will pray, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Forgive us and our fellow believers who preceded us in faith, and do not allow bitterness into our hearts towards those who believe. Our Lord! Indeed, You are Ever Gracious, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"